      <h2>JennAir range repair — common questions</h2>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>F1, F1-1, F1-7 — what's the difference?</summary>
        <p>F1 = general ignition fault (try 10-min reset). F1-1 = oven sensor or ERC ($165-$245 or $485-$680). F1-7 = touchpad ribbon cable (common on 2004-2010 LA coastal units, $145-$215 ribbon or $385-$545 touchpad).</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Burner won't ignite — first check?</summary>
        <p>Listen for clicking. Clicking = spark OK, check burner ports / cap alignment (often free fix). No clicking = spark module $285-$385 or electrode $95-$145. Manual light with long match while waiting.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>JDRP vs JGRP vs JIS/JPIGC — which?</summary>
        <p>JDRP = dual-fuel (gas cooktop + electric oven), most popular LA. JDSP = newer dual-fuel with Steam Assist. JGRP = all-gas pro. JIS = consumer induction slide-in. JPIFC / JPIGC = pro induction (launched late 2024). Suffix HL = RISE, HM = NOIR. Different failure modes and service costs per platform.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>My range is 15+ years — worth repairing?</summary>
        <p>Depends on component. Sensor ($165-$245) or spark module ($285-$385) = yes, clear ROI. ERC ($485-$680) = borderline. Compound $1,200+ repairs on pre-2010 units = honest replacement discussion.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>How much does JennAir range repair cost?</summary>
        <p>Diagnostic $89, waived with repair. Common: oven sensor $165-$245, spark module $285-$385, convection fan $285-$425, ERC $485-$680, hinge pair $320-$460. Full pricing above.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </section>

